From df2d2e0e000a4893ba85ff5a9810b7c046a9f624 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Tue, 9 Jun 2026 20:08:21 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Fix hCaptcha integration
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

- CSP: allow hCaptcha origins (js.hcaptcha.com, *.hcaptcha.com) in
  script-src, style-src, connect-src, frame-src, child-src — without
  this the captcha could never render under the existing CSP
- Drop the conflicting web3forms.com/client/script.js loader; our
  src.js submit handler already POSTs directly to Web3Forms, so two
  interceptors were fighting each other
- Load hCaptcha API directly (js.hcaptcha.com/1/api.js) and switch the
  captcha div from data-captcha="true" (Web3Forms-loader convention) to
  the standard data-sitekey attribute using Web3Forms' public sitekey
- Move the captcha widget from the top of each form down to just above
  the submit button (better UX, doesn't push the form fields down)
- Replace the null-deref captcha check in src.js (the textarea doesn't
  exist before the widget mounts) with a safe lookup; if the captcha
  isn't solved, show a friendly message via the existing popup instead
  of a browser alert()
- Add a small captcha-field style so the widget centers and scales on
  very narrow phones

https://claude.ai/code/session_01CQhaur5bgTcTG5y3ok9zon
